geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: The intersection of the vertical axis of a 5/8" Whitworth threaded steel stub, with the horizontal plane coinciding with the top of the mounting plate to which the steel stub is attached. This mounting is on top of the north calibration pillar at the Stromlo satellite Laser Ranging station, and is 183mm vertically above a similar mounting which is used for the Laser calibration target. This mounting for the calibration target is known as AU046.
